1
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:31,830
[The Dark Romance]

2
00:01:32,180 --> 00:01:34,920
[Episode 9]

3
00:01:36,789 --> 00:01:38,390
This topic is very valuable.

4
00:01:39,640 --> 00:01:41,100
How did you come up with it?

5
00:01:41,479 --> 00:01:42,759
Before, when we were at the beach,

6
00:01:42,759 --> 00:01:44,400
you asked me to write something,

7
00:01:44,400 --> 00:01:45,590
and I started wondering

8
00:01:45,590 --> 00:01:48,720
where those characters
were eventually carried off to.

9
00:01:50,550 --> 00:01:51,340
Look.

10
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,789
In the second section here,

11
00:01:54,789 --> 00:01:56,670
you should first provide

12
00:01:56,920 --> 00:01:58,520
a summary of the wave theory.

13
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:01,310
For example, the randomness of waves,

14
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,560
the theory of
small-amplitude wave fluctuations,

15
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:06,200
numerical simulation methods
for waves, and so on.

16
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:07,500
From this foundation,

17
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:09,430
you can then move into your own argument.

18
00:02:09,430 --> 00:02:09,979
Okay.

19
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:12,000
I'll go back and think it over.

20
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:13,930
I'll show you once I've revised it.

21
00:02:14,800 --> 00:02:15,150
Keep it up.

22
00:02:15,150 --> 00:02:16,210
Thank you, Ms. Yan.

23
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:17,800
Director Lin.

24
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,000
Hello, Director Lin.

25
00:02:20,079 --> 00:02:21,800
I heard you've been working
really hard recently,

26
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,730
spending every day in the library.

27
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:27,079
Her paper outline is well written.

28
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,560
If she puts in the effort,

29
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:30,360
it should turn out to be
a pretty valuable paper.

30
00:02:30,360 --> 00:02:30,820
Not bad.

31
00:02:30,910 --> 00:02:31,510
Well done.

32
00:02:31,870 --> 00:02:33,130
Hurry up and finish it,

33
00:02:33,310 --> 00:02:35,079
so you can graduate with everyone else.

34
00:02:35,079 --> 00:02:35,410
Okay.

35
00:02:35,710 --> 00:02:36,710
Thank you, Director Lin.

36
00:02:36,710 --> 00:02:37,430
Thank you, Ms. Yan.

37
00:02:37,430 --> 00:02:38,760
I'll take my leave then.

38
00:02:43,079 --> 00:02:44,120
I hope this child

39
00:02:44,750 --> 00:02:46,150
is worthy of your help.

40
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:50,200
Well, this is just
what a teacher should do, right?

41
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,010
Please sit, Director.

42
00:02:54,010 --> 00:02:54,670
You sit too.

43
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:58,910
Here's the thing,

44
00:02:58,910 --> 00:02:59,430
Ms. Yan.

45
00:02:59,910 --> 00:03:01,010
Next month,

46
00:03:01,430 --> 00:03:03,960
there's going to be a scholarship
donation program in our school.

47
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:06,080
The administration is currently
coordinating it.

48
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:08,280
But considering relevance to majors—

49
00:03:08,680 --> 00:03:10,840
especially that
our Oceanography Department

50
00:03:10,840 --> 00:03:11,870
has made outstanding achievements

51
00:03:11,870 --> 00:03:12,930
in talent training

52
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:14,240
and discipline development

53
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,120
over the years—

54
00:03:15,840 --> 00:03:17,000
the scholarship

55
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:19,800
will be somewhat prioritized
for our department.

56
00:03:21,120 --> 00:03:24,160
A scholarship is a good thing
for the students.

57
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:27,000
This is a long-term project,

58
00:03:27,030 --> 00:03:29,360
and on behalf of the department,
we want to

59
00:03:29,560 --> 00:03:31,290
assign you to take charge of it.

60
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:32,000
Me?

61
00:03:33,079 --> 00:03:33,800
Ms. Yan.

62
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:35,360
The school

63
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:36,400
knows that

64
00:03:36,750 --> 00:03:38,400
what happened with Li Changning

65
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:39,680
caused you some unfair treatment

66
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:42,680
and affected this year's
professional title evaluation.

67
00:03:42,680 --> 00:03:44,000
Your overall ability is strong,

68
00:03:44,000 --> 00:03:45,520
and you care about the students—

69
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,780
this is evident to all.

70
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:48,630
In next year's evaluation,

71
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:50,360
there will definitely be no problem.

72
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,400
We certainly don't want to miss out

73
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:52,530
on a talent like you.

74
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,190
So you mean

75
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:57,500
I can be reappointed as usual?

76
00:03:57,550 --> 00:03:57,860
Yes.

77
00:03:58,400 --> 00:03:59,800
Here, take a look at this.

78
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:03,000
The other party

79
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:04,860
is a maritime logistics company.

80
00:04:04,870 --> 00:04:06,660
If the talk goes well,

81
00:04:07,190 --> 00:04:08,560
besides the scholarship,

82
00:04:08,560 --> 00:04:09,290
we might even

83
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,080
be able to help secure jobs

84
00:04:11,080 --> 00:04:12,540
for some of our graduates.

85
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:15,400
I have to say,

86
00:04:15,400 --> 00:04:16,180
that Mr. Ding

87
00:04:16,269 --> 00:04:17,399
has quite a good eye.

88
00:04:17,550 --> 00:04:18,610
[Project Information]

89
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:20,470
He said he met you at an academic seminar

90
00:04:18,630 --> 00:04:20,329
[Project Name:
Xinghan Scholarship Donation Program]

91
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:21,720
and had a very good impression of you.

92
00:04:21,720 --> 00:04:22,630
He even specifically proposed

93
00:04:22,630 --> 00:04:24,040
that you serve as

94
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:26,360
a member of
this scholarship review committee.

95
00:04:24,260 --> 00:04:25,260
[Donor: Oceanvision International Group]

96
00:04:25,270 --> 00:04:26,610
[Recipient:
Li Hai University of Science and Technology]

97
00:04:26,650 --> 00:04:30,440
[Lihai Mingde International Hospital]

98
00:04:28,510 --> 00:04:30,170
What's this supposed to mean?

99
00:04:30,720 --> 00:04:31,850
Even if I lose my job,

100
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,940
I wouldn't accept any handouts from you.

101
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:37,010
I'm really speechless.

102
00:04:38,390 --> 00:04:39,870
It's only you and your mom

103
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,500
that I can't get mad at.

104
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,120
If it were anyone else,

105
00:04:43,120 --> 00:04:43,920
go ask around—

106
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,409
who would dare talk to me like that?

107
00:04:50,630 --> 00:04:52,390
Your mom called to beg me.

108
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:54,950
Seeing the genuine sincerity in her,

109
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:56,190
I really felt for her.

110
00:04:57,140 --> 00:04:57,920
I didn't expect that

111
00:04:57,920 --> 00:05:00,120
my good intentions totally backfired.

112
00:05:00,920 --> 00:05:03,360
What was the point of me
spending that 10 million then—

113
00:05:03,360 --> 00:05:05,690
just so you could
take your anger out on me?

114
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:07,900
You said my mom came to beg you?

115
00:05:08,070 --> 00:05:08,730
What else?

116
00:05:09,270 --> 00:05:11,730
Your mom said
you were going to lose your job.

117
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:15,560
Why did you do this?

118
00:05:16,950 --> 00:05:19,600
Why did you call him
to talk about my situation?

119
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,650
Why are you losing your temper?

120
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,190
Your Uncle Ding called and said

121
00:05:24,190 --> 00:05:26,320
that your job issue has been resolved.

122
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,520
I don't need him to
resolve my job issues for me.

123
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,430
Didn't I tell you

124
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:36,070
that the school didn't say
they wanted me to leave?

125
00:05:36,070 --> 00:05:37,600
From now on, if you have any thoughts

126
00:05:37,600 --> 00:05:38,680
about my matters,

127
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:41,460
can you come and talk to me directly?

128
00:05:41,490 --> 00:05:42,890
What should I talk to you?

129
00:05:43,800 --> 00:05:44,860
You are already 36,

130
00:05:45,060 --> 00:05:47,630
just like me, spending half your life
as a struggling teacher,

131
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:49,630
and you even have a child to support.

132
00:05:49,870 --> 00:05:51,730
If the school were to kick you out,

133
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,860
who would hire you?

134
00:05:53,700 --> 00:05:55,070
You're unwilling to ask for help,

135
00:05:55,070 --> 00:05:57,120
so I swallowed my pride to plead for you.

136
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,450
Did I do anything wrong?

137
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:02,870
But you didn't consider my feelings, Mom.

138
00:06:05,390 --> 00:06:07,390
He donated 10 million to the school.

139
00:06:09,520 --> 00:06:11,630
He donated 10 million for your sake?

140
00:06:12,240 --> 00:06:14,770
Our family couldn't repay it
in generations.

141
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:18,360
Your Uncle Ding is truly
loyal and affectionate.

142
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:20,430
He treats you like his own daughter.

143
00:06:30,800 --> 00:06:32,270
So I have to owe him for a lifetime,

144
00:06:32,270 --> 00:06:32,830
right?

145
00:06:34,950 --> 00:06:35,980
Whatever he says,

146
00:06:36,390 --> 00:06:37,480
I have to listen to him.

147
00:06:37,480 --> 00:06:38,409
Is that how it is?

148
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:40,170
How can you say that?

149
00:06:40,230 --> 00:06:42,040
You really don't know what's good for you!

150
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:42,950
Even though he's so ill,

151
00:06:42,950 --> 00:06:44,159
he still cares about your matters.

152
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,000
It's only right

153
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,720
if you honor him

154
00:06:46,870 --> 00:06:48,270
like an elder in the family.

155
00:06:48,270 --> 00:06:50,400
Back then, you caused your dad's death

156
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:52,390
when he came back to visit.

157
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,190
It didn't even count as a work injury.

158
00:06:54,190 --> 00:06:55,360
In the end, it was your Uncle Ding

159
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:57,570
who helped us secure the compensation.

160
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,680
And after your high school entrance exam,

161
00:06:59,680 --> 00:07:01,680
wasn't it your Uncle Ding who ran around

162
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:02,610
pulling strings

163
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:03,430
to get you into

164
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:05,230
the provincial key high school?

165
00:07:06,070 --> 00:07:07,930
You should be grateful, Yan Ling.

166
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,680
It's true that you did quite well,

167
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:14,830
but at most, that would have gotten you
into a key school in our city.

168
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:17,190
But Uncle Ding got you into

169
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:18,560
a provincial key school.

170
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:20,050
That took a lot of effort.

171
00:07:21,360 --> 00:07:23,360
Uncle Ding's kindness to our family

172
00:07:23,370 --> 00:07:26,030
is something we could never repay
in a lifetime.

173
00:07:26,830 --> 00:07:28,520
We have to show gratitude.

174
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:49,310
Miss!

175
00:07:49,750 --> 00:07:51,950
Your phone has been ringing for a while.

176
00:08:02,950 --> 00:08:05,390
Ms. Yan, I saw him again.

177
00:08:08,870 --> 00:08:09,960
Changning!

178
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:12,450
Li Changning!

179
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:19,080
Don't do anything stupid, Changning!

180
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:20,520
Li Changning!

181
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,390
Li Changning!

182
00:08:27,390 --> 00:08:28,430
Get back here!

183
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,880
Get back here!

184
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:34,960
Get back here! Come back with me!

185
00:08:34,960 --> 00:08:36,240
Get back here! Come back with me!

186
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,390
I'm not trying to kill myself,

187
00:08:37,390 --> 00:08:37,980
Ms. Yan!

188
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:39,490
I'm not trying to kill myself!

189
00:08:39,490 --> 00:08:41,000
I just want to wash away

190
00:08:41,000 --> 00:08:43,630
the shameful and stupid things
he left on me!

191
00:08:44,630 --> 00:08:45,660
-Wash them all away!
-Changning!

192
00:08:45,660 --> 00:08:46,640
Wash them away!

193
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,100
Changning!

194
00:08:52,150 --> 00:08:53,470
Come back with me!

195
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:55,380
So close.

196
00:08:56,350 --> 00:08:57,790
How could you bring her here?

197
00:08:57,790 --> 00:08:59,360
You said this place belongs to us—

198
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,200
just the two of us!

199
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:00,670
What are you doing?

200
00:09:00,670 --> 00:09:01,030
Stop it.

201
00:09:01,030 --> 00:09:02,200
I broke up with you a long time ago.

202
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,800
I do want to break up with you!

203
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:05,270
I came here just to

204
00:09:05,270 --> 00:09:07,070
make a clean break with the past.

205
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,530
But how could you...

206
00:09:09,270 --> 00:09:10,200
How could you...

207
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,210
I thought

208
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:14,200
when a relationship ends

209
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:15,120
and fades away,

210
00:09:15,340 --> 00:09:17,610
at least the good parts would remain.

211
00:09:18,180 --> 00:09:20,530
But he denied everything between us—

212
00:09:20,600 --> 00:09:22,270
he denied our past,

213
00:09:22,360 --> 00:09:23,960
and he completely denied me!

214
00:09:24,030 --> 00:09:25,630
Your stupidity disgusts me!

215
00:09:26,350 --> 00:09:27,120
What makes you

216
00:09:27,120 --> 00:09:28,320
think you deserve me?

217
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:30,960
Just because you slept with me?

218
00:09:30,960 --> 00:09:31,960
Country bumpkin.

219
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,790
Look at yourself, you hillbilly.

220
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:35,610
What right do you have to talk to me
about love?

221
00:09:35,610 --> 00:09:36,670
It's not like that.

222
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:37,550
It's not like that.

223
00:09:37,550 --> 00:09:38,270
It is!

224
00:09:38,270 --> 00:09:39,390
It just is!

225
00:09:40,140 --> 00:09:40,970
Changning!

226
00:09:41,630 --> 00:09:42,290
Changning!

227
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:44,390
Changning!

228
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:46,230
He bullied me and humiliated me

229
00:09:46,480 --> 00:09:47,410
again and again.

230
00:09:47,710 --> 00:09:48,830
Yes, yes—

231
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:51,220
I am indeed heartbroken,

232
00:09:51,390 --> 00:09:53,600
but that's because
I finally saw clearly that

233
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:56,060
what I fell in love with
wasn't even a person!

234
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,480
He's a devil.

235
00:09:57,510 --> 00:09:58,670
He's a beast!

236
00:10:01,510 --> 00:10:02,320
Ms. Yan.

237
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,750
I heard from the school

238
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:06,870
that you took the disciplinary action
in my place.

239
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:08,130
You saved me.

240
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,990
A large part of the new me

241
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:12,600
is because of you.

242
00:10:13,720 --> 00:10:15,000
I will absolutely never

243
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:17,670
let that beast break me again!

244
00:10:18,600 --> 00:10:19,420
You said

245
00:10:19,510 --> 00:10:21,320
that everything will get better,

246
00:10:21,320 --> 00:10:22,840
that everything will pass,

247
00:10:22,840 --> 00:10:24,700
and I'll live well and keep going,

248
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:25,840
right?

249
00:10:26,750 --> 00:10:27,360
Right?

250
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:32,400
Everything will be fine.

251
00:10:32,890 --> 00:10:34,490
Everything will get better.

252
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:37,440
You must live well, Changning.

253
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:39,730
Don't let the beasts

254
00:10:41,360 --> 00:10:42,670
break us again.

255
00:10:58,080 --> 00:10:59,150
This is the first time

256
00:10:59,150 --> 00:11:00,030
our school has received

257
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:01,360
a large donation

258
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,380
from society.

259
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:03,320
Secretary Yu

260
00:11:03,320 --> 00:11:04,960
and the rest of us all
take this very seriously.

261
00:11:04,960 --> 00:11:05,760
Director Lin,

262
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:07,480
please come up with a set of

263
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,770
selection rules for the scholarship
as soon as possible.

264
00:11:09,770 --> 00:11:11,200
After all, Oceanvision International

265
00:11:11,200 --> 00:11:12,390
proposed to favor your

266
00:11:12,390 --> 00:11:14,390
Department of Atmospheric
and Oceanic Sciences.

267
00:11:14,390 --> 00:11:15,050
No problem.

268
00:11:15,760 --> 00:11:17,220
Ms. Yan from our department

269
00:11:17,220 --> 00:11:19,680
is already a member
of the review committee.

270
00:11:19,930 --> 00:11:22,410
I will draft a plan with her
as soon as possible

271
00:11:22,410 --> 00:11:24,010
and then submit it to the college

272
00:11:24,010 --> 00:11:26,030
and the review committee
for feedback and guidance.

273
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:26,850
Secretary Yu,

274
00:11:27,030 --> 00:11:27,890
President Sun.

275
00:11:28,360 --> 00:11:30,630
I feel my ability and qualifications

276
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:33,490
are far behind
the other committee members.

277
00:11:33,770 --> 00:11:36,420
So I won't be participating in

278
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:38,220
the scholarship review this time.

279
00:11:38,220 --> 00:11:38,860
Ms. Yan.

280
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:42,500
Mr. Ding from Oceanvision International
specifically requested you,

281
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:44,760
which means he thinks you are qualified.

282
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:48,290
Many senior professors here
are more qualified than me.

283
00:11:48,290 --> 00:11:49,750
I'm still just a lecturer.

284
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:51,670
It's really inappropriate.

285
00:11:52,130 --> 00:11:52,800
Ms. Yan,

286
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:54,770
are you asking for a promotion?

287
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:58,080
Director Lin should have told you.

288
00:11:58,410 --> 00:11:59,100
This year,

289
00:11:59,200 --> 00:12:00,720
the matter with Li Changning

290
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,980
has affected you.

291
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,110
For next year's professional title review,

292
00:12:03,110 --> 00:12:05,170
we'll make sure to give you priority.

293
00:12:05,430 --> 00:12:06,070
No, no, no.

294
00:12:06,090 --> 00:12:07,410
That's really not what I meant.

295
00:12:07,410 --> 00:12:09,610
I genuinely feel I'm not qualified yet.

296
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:10,600
Leaders,

297
00:12:11,050 --> 00:12:12,120
after the meeting,

298
00:12:12,140 --> 00:12:15,140
-I'll talk to Ms. Yan...
-Thank you for your generous support,

299
00:12:15,140 --> 00:12:16,600
but I really can't serve as

300
00:12:17,450 --> 00:12:19,380
a member of this review committee.

301
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:22,090
In that case,

302
00:12:22,470 --> 00:12:23,870
we won't force it.

303
00:12:24,130 --> 00:12:26,530
We will respect Ms. Yan's personal wishes.

304
00:12:28,310 --> 00:12:29,370
Let's call it a day.

305
00:13:04,130 --> 00:13:04,860
You're back.

306
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:06,760
Hurry up and wash your hands.

307
00:13:06,760 --> 00:13:07,690
Get ready to eat.

308
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:11,180
Not bad.

309
00:13:17,680 --> 00:13:18,730
Dr. Luo?

310
00:13:19,590 --> 00:13:20,190
Ms. Yan.

311
00:13:20,850 --> 00:13:22,010
Why are you here?

312
00:13:23,660 --> 00:13:25,450
Cola threw up several times.

313
00:13:25,470 --> 00:13:27,130
You didn't answer your phone,

314
00:13:27,190 --> 00:13:28,710
so I called Dr. Luo.

315
00:13:28,960 --> 00:13:30,680
He sounded worried on the phone,

316
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:32,670
so I rushed over without telling you.

317
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:33,000
Well,

318
00:13:33,300 --> 00:13:35,010
is Cola okay now?

319
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,160
Dr. Luo said

320
00:13:36,160 --> 00:13:37,370
it just ate too much.

321
00:13:38,760 --> 00:13:40,620
Jiale just spoiled Cola too much.

322
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:42,830
I discussed it with Jiale today

323
00:13:43,090 --> 00:13:43,520
to see if we could

324
00:13:43,520 --> 00:13:44,610
let him raise

325
00:13:44,610 --> 00:13:45,540
Cola from now on.

326
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,330
Can I?

327
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:51,330
How about this?

328
00:13:52,740 --> 00:13:54,080
I'll pay you.

329
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:55,490
Jiale told me

330
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,020
this kind of hamster is quite expensive.

331
00:13:59,190 --> 00:14:00,680
It's indeed quite expensive.

332
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,340
One is about over 50,000 yuan.

333
00:14:02,880 --> 00:14:03,850
That expensive?

334
00:14:07,800 --> 00:14:09,160
You two are indeed mother and son.

335
00:14:09,160 --> 00:14:11,820
Your shocked expressions
are exactly the same.

336
00:14:12,160 --> 00:14:12,800
Ms. Yan,

337
00:14:13,370 --> 00:14:15,280
I've already come to cook at your house.

338
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:17,410
Could you not treat me like a stranger?

339
00:14:19,520 --> 00:14:20,250
Then go on

340
00:14:20,250 --> 00:14:21,280
and thank Dr. Luo.

341
00:14:21,850 --> 00:14:22,910
Thank you, Dr. Luo.

342
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:23,850
You're welcome.

343
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:26,850
I'll put the tableware and stuff

344
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:27,880
over there first.

345
00:14:28,160 --> 00:14:28,880
Thanks.

346
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:33,520
Ms. Yan.

347
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:34,880
There's only one dish left to finish.

348
00:14:34,880 --> 00:14:35,550
I'll be quick.

349
00:14:35,550 --> 00:14:36,610
Just wait a moment.

350
00:14:37,040 --> 00:14:38,240
I'm really sorry.

351
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:40,920
I should be treating you to a meal,

352
00:14:41,370 --> 00:14:43,300
but now you're here cooking for me.

353
00:14:43,370 --> 00:14:44,490
It's the least I could do.

354
00:14:44,490 --> 00:14:44,820
Here.

355
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:48,260
After all, Jiale has been taking care of
my Cola for so long.

356
00:14:48,260 --> 00:14:49,400
It's just a meal.

357
00:14:50,690 --> 00:14:51,560
He told me

358
00:14:52,130 --> 00:14:53,040
he really craves

359
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,400
his godmother's home-cooked meals,

360
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:57,330
and he hasn't had a proper meal
at home for a long time.

361
00:15:01,160 --> 00:15:02,490
The garlic is...

362
00:15:02,950 --> 00:15:03,820
It's in the fridge, right?

363
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:04,730
Yes, I'll get it.

364
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:05,330
It's okay.

365
00:15:07,110 --> 00:15:07,850
Here it is.

366
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:10,160
Is this enough?

367
00:15:16,610 --> 00:15:17,670
Are you using this?

368
00:15:18,920 --> 00:15:20,560
I get tinnitus sometimes.

369
00:15:21,470 --> 00:15:22,470
It's an old issue.

370
00:15:23,250 --> 00:15:24,560
If it's not organic,

371
00:15:24,680 --> 00:15:27,090
this condition is most likely
related to stress.

372
00:15:27,090 --> 00:15:27,850
If you have the time,

373
00:15:27,850 --> 00:15:29,310
you should go see a doctor.

374
00:15:44,010 --> 00:15:45,870
Is there anything I can help with?

375
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:48,340
Right. There's one more dish.

376
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:52,730
Sweet and sour spare ribs.

377
00:15:52,730 --> 00:15:54,590
Jiale said he really craves this.

378
00:16:25,530 --> 00:16:26,400
Thank you.

379
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:28,640
You are a very good cook.

380
00:16:29,300 --> 00:16:30,050
Am I?

381
00:16:31,640 --> 00:16:33,530
And what's especially coincidental is that

382
00:16:33,530 --> 00:16:34,400
Leilei

383
00:16:34,890 --> 00:16:37,630
used to always add dried plums

384
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,880
when making this dish too.

385
00:16:41,970 --> 00:16:44,170
Actually, it was Jiale who told me that.

386
00:16:44,760 --> 00:16:46,690
He said you only eat the plums in it.

387
00:16:49,500 --> 00:16:50,560
If you guys like it,

388
00:16:51,250 --> 00:16:52,310
I'll make it for you

389
00:16:52,650 --> 00:16:54,250
whenever I have time.

390
00:16:59,850 --> 00:17:01,580
I actually came to see you today

391
00:17:01,640 --> 00:17:03,370
to talk to you about something.

392
00:17:03,530 --> 00:17:04,730
But with Jiale there,

393
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:06,290
it wasn't very convenient.

394
00:17:08,970 --> 00:17:10,170
You mentioned before

395
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,839
that Yu Kexin

396
00:17:12,450 --> 00:17:14,650
also had that tattoo on her body, right?

397
00:17:16,619 --> 00:17:16,970
Yes.

398
00:17:18,599 --> 00:17:19,800
I took a closer look

399
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:21,329
at the syllabus you sent me.

400
00:17:21,800 --> 00:17:22,839
Branding tattoos

401
00:17:22,839 --> 00:17:24,099
is one of the chapters.

402
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:25,310
I was thinking,

403
00:17:25,579 --> 00:17:25,970
maybe those people

404
00:17:25,970 --> 00:17:28,359
make their other half get
specific patterns tattooed

405
00:17:28,359 --> 00:17:31,020
to show their possession and control
over them.

406
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:36,760
You mean

407
00:17:38,650 --> 00:17:39,560
Yu Kexin

408
00:17:40,320 --> 00:17:42,780
might also have been a victim
from back then,

409
00:17:43,210 --> 00:17:44,010
but then,

410
00:17:45,170 --> 00:17:46,650
she chose to join them

411
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,610
and keep deceiving others?

412
00:17:50,140 --> 00:17:51,120
Very likely.

413
00:17:55,360 --> 00:17:58,170
Actually, I planned to call you
to tell you about this,

414
00:17:58,170 --> 00:18:00,360
but Jiale suddenly sent me
a WeChat message,

415
00:18:00,360 --> 00:18:02,540
so I ended up coming to your house
to cook first.

416
00:18:02,540 --> 00:18:04,000
I hope this tiny bit of clue

417
00:18:04,760 --> 00:18:06,320
could be of some help to you—
though I'm not sure.

418
00:18:06,320 --> 00:18:07,720
It is. Of course it is.

419
00:18:08,730 --> 00:18:09,600
Thank you.

420
00:18:13,580 --> 00:18:15,310
You said those two words again.

421
00:18:15,910 --> 00:18:16,910
"Thank you."

422
00:18:22,820 --> 00:18:24,550
Calmly accepting others' help

423
00:18:24,930 --> 00:18:26,330
and learning to be loved—

424
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:27,690
I think

425
00:18:28,600 --> 00:18:31,200
these are very important lessons
in our lives,

426
00:18:31,490 --> 00:18:32,050
right?

427
00:18:44,250 --> 00:18:45,110
Go back inside.

428
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:47,700
It's getting cold.

429
00:18:53,040 --> 00:18:53,610
Well,

430
00:18:54,360 --> 00:18:56,090
be careful on your way back too.

431
00:18:56,510 --> 00:18:56,930
I will.

432
00:18:59,760 --> 00:19:00,490
I'm leaving.

433
00:19:25,080 --> 00:19:28,080
It's so late. Why haven't you
gone to take a shower yet?

434
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:29,210
Although Dr. Luo

435
00:19:29,210 --> 00:19:30,740
likes to preach a little bit

436
00:19:31,320 --> 00:19:32,450
and opens up easily,

437
00:19:33,730 --> 00:19:34,010
if you

438
00:19:34,010 --> 00:19:36,120
really want to be with him,

439
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:37,000
I won't object.

440
00:19:37,840 --> 00:19:39,900
What nonsense are you talking about?

441
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,370
We are just friends.

442
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:43,090
Oh right,

443
00:19:43,840 --> 00:19:45,280
when you couldn't reach me,

444
00:19:45,280 --> 00:19:46,960
why didn't you call your dad?

445
00:19:47,450 --> 00:19:48,450
Don't mention it.

446
00:19:48,970 --> 00:19:51,210
Miss Fang Fang texted me this afternoon,

447
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:54,040
asking if my dad is working overtime
every day this week.

448
00:19:54,040 --> 00:19:55,570
That shouldn't be the case.

449
00:19:56,170 --> 00:19:58,800
Even if the meteorological bureau
is dealing with the flood season

450
00:19:58,800 --> 00:20:00,330
and operates 24 hours a day,

451
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,730
they still rotate shifts every 3 days.

452
00:20:02,730 --> 00:20:05,010
There's no way he wouldn't be seen
at all every day.

453
00:20:05,010 --> 00:20:06,070
So what did you say?

454
00:20:06,410 --> 00:20:07,620
Well, I could only

455
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,600
cover for him for now.

456
00:20:11,410 --> 00:20:12,360
Yan Jiale.

457
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,000
So you've even learned

458
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,930
to lie right to people's faces now?

459
00:20:17,690 --> 00:20:20,010
Godmother said this is called a white lie.

460
00:20:20,010 --> 00:20:20,560
Besides,

461
00:20:20,580 --> 00:20:22,950
my dad wouldn't do anything bad.

462
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:24,150
I guess

463
00:20:24,540 --> 00:20:26,170
he's just busy trying to clear

464
00:20:26,170 --> 00:20:28,300
the new map of Last Island of Survival.

465
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:31,840
You're right.

466
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:33,490
I'll reflect on myself.

467
00:20:33,650 --> 00:20:35,450
From now on, if I handle something badly,

468
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:36,650
remember to remind me

469
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:37,730
how your godmother would handle it,

470
00:20:37,730 --> 00:20:38,410
okay?

471
00:20:43,710 --> 00:20:45,400
[The Art of Love—
Exploring the Mysteries of Love]

472
00:20:44,570 --> 00:20:45,680
This is Hajun.

